==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invariable
<hw>In*va"ri*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>variable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>invariable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not given to variation or change;
unalterable; unchangeable; always uniform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Physical laws which are <qex>invariable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*va"ri*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*va"ri*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invariable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Invariable
<hw>In*va"ri*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>An invariable quantity; a constant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>invariably</ent>⟦br⟧
